OL,7,FThe family of a young mother who died
OL,8,Ffrom cervical cancer after she was
OL,9,Ftold she was too young for a smear
OL,10,Ftest are calling for changes to
OL,11,Fguidelines which they believe may have
OL,12,Fgiven her a fighting chance of
OL,13,Fsurvival.JJody Oxley, a mum of two
OL,14,Ffrom , died in January at the age of
OL,15,F29. She had been denied a smear test
OL,16,Fseven years earlier because she was
OL,17,Funder 25 - even though she had
OL,18,Fsymptoms of the disease.
